channel.title: Web Design Contest for my site
channel.description:
Hey guys, I'm starting up a web design contest for my web site.
Back-end scripting is not required, but a simple image gallery/news poster would be OK (but I could do that myself) What I'm looking for is a well graphical web design, nothing too graphic intensive though. You really need to have a creative side for this. - Top left hand corner a parkour-type vectored image, nav and left side nav (KEEP PSD's!!) and a middle section for content - colours preferably green/black/white (simplistic colours considering most of it will be vectored)
What you get:
[ul][li]Invites to 3 great torrent websites (SceneAccess, IPTorrents, Libble)[/li] [li]A title on the forums provided-without permission, mind you- by Niall ;)[/li] [li]Affiliates/small button on my site to yours[/li] [li]Will come up with more, possibly prize $$[/li][/ul]
I'll post when the qualifying rounds are over, etc..
Comments/questions may be posted in this topic, along with current submissions (which there shouldn't be any soon)
Also post here if you think you'll be willing to do this, so I can keep track of users that are going to submit
[size=7pt]gtfo it's almost 1 am, may revise topic tomorrow[/size]
As a side note to help you in the competition, here's some styles I like/would like to see in the design: http://hmb-design.deviantart.com/art/Parkour-41195211 http://cliq.deviantart.com/art/parkour-39564761 http://jackwaters.deviantart.com/art/Parkour-35803398 http://retroweapon.deviantart.com/art/le-parkour-42764845
[b]NEW! You could also go for a grunge style, a sporty, intense look[/b]
